CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 1, 1941, pg. 8, reads: "These ladies are leaders in present YWCA Drive. Here they are talking over the final plans for that last spurt which will pit them over the top.  They are, left to right: Mesdames J. A. Waytes, Robert Thompson, Earl Hord, Henry Parker, Edward Lampkins, co-chairman; Arthur Taylor, chairman; Mrs. Walter Brice. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. J. A. Waytes, Mrs. Robert Thompson, Rema Hord, Mrs. Henry Parker, Mrs. Edward Lampkins, Mrs. Arthur Taylor, and Mrs. Walter Brice, gathered around square table with documents for meeting about YWCA fundraising drive
